Oct 1 2009 	Comfort affordability pleasant and imaginative surroundings	My wife and I both were pleasantly surprised by the imaginative conversion of this old Japan Town hotel into a delightfully whimsical and creative space. The murals in the rooms with comment in Japanese characters, the photographs of staff in costume in the elevator and restaurant, the responsive and pleasant personnel, the convenient proximity of the hotel to the inviting features of Japan Town, the relaxed informality of everything, to say nothing of affordability and easy public transportation to all locations at our door - all made our stay at this hotel one of our best experiences ever in visiting San Francisco. What a revelation to find a hotel chain, Best Western, having the imagination to allow 'Pop' and other innovative Japanese artists seemingly free reign to design and decorate this formerly undistinguished hotel.	
