Jul 12 2009 	Watch out for unscrupulous charging practices.	I chose this hotel because it is only 4 blocks from the hospital where my brother had emergency surgery. It is a clean hotel at a reasonable price. After my third night here I found out that they had already debited my checking account for more than $800. What a surprise, since the rate was approximately $90/night including taxes and fees.Here's what they explained to me:The company policy is to charge your credit card for the entire length of your reservation when you arrive. In addition, they charge an additional $50 per night for possible &quot;incidental&quot; expenses! When you check out, if you have not stayed the entire time, or used any &quot;incidentals,&quot; your bank will release the funds not spent. These policies are not posted or printed, nor did the person who told me to reserve an entire week and cancel the nights I don't need later.I have stayed in many hotels in throughout the US and in Europe and have never experienced this before. In the future I would not stay at this hotel again because they do not inform the guests of this policy.	
Jun 30 2009 	Hotel Tomo is convenient and well-appointed with excellent service.	We had a wonderful 4-night stay at Hotel Tomo. Our room on the sixth floor was bright, clean, beautifully decorated in a Japanese motif, and very quiet -- no street noise at all, although it is located on a busy street (Sutter). Japan Town is directly across the street and is full of great restaurants in all price ranges. Also across the street is a bus line that goes directly to Union Square and Market Street. (Seniors unfamiliar with San Francisco should be aware that the senior rate is 50 cents to ride anywhere on the bus.)Service at Hotel Tomo was really excellent. Several times we called for replacement items of Kleenex, etc., and housekeeping was at our door within minutes. There were at least two people manning the reception desk at all times, so we never had to wait in line if we had a question. Two additional bonuses: Free wireless internet (or the desk will also provide a cable), and a very nice &quot;Little Gym&quot; with a rubberized floor, mats, free weights, a treadmill, an elyptical, and a bike.There were only two very minor things that were a bit less than satisfactory to us. One, the room doors were impossible to close without that final &quot;slam,&quot; so as late sleepers, we were awakened around 7:45 each morning as other guests began leaving their rooms. Secondly, we ate breakfast two mornings in the hotel restaurant, and we found it to be a bit on the greasy side. All in all, our stay at Hotel Tomo was wonderful, and a very, very good value for the money. We've stayed in many San Francisco hotels, but I think from now on, depending on their rates at the time, this one will be our first choice -- especially since it's just a short walk to our daughter's condo!	
