y exit door (right out side my room door) while he repeatedly went out for a smoke allowing his smoke fill the halls and rooms of the 2nd floor. After 2 hours of the increasingly intense smell of smoke I requested another room, since my daughter is asthmatic. So... on our final evening under unfortunate conditions we were put in a room on the 7th floor (of the 8 floor bldg) with an actual balcony and better view which overlooked the city.[I contacted Best Western to report how rudely I was treated upon arrival. The hotel manager contacted me and instead of voluntarily offering some sort of gesture to recompense for their poor service she asked that I tell her what I wanted. Ultimately, I received a trivial discount, which hardly gave me the desire to return to their hotel.]Again, the contemporary decor was nice. Also, the hotel was clean and the neighborhood was quiet and serene.	
